Sifco SA, a Brazilian auto-parts
maker, plans to meet with bond investors tomorrow through July
30, according to a person familiar with the talks.  Banco Pine SA, Citigroup Inc. and Goldman Sachs Group Inc.
are arranging the meetings, said the person, who asked not to be
identified because he is not authorized to speak publicly.  To contact the reporter on this story:
